          "ANALYSIS": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "INTED"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " Measurements of neutron spectra were made  at",
                " five  angles between 50 and 146 degrees.  Because of",
                " the 2.9 MeV separation between the ground state  and",
                " first  excited  state of Be-8,  kinematics enables a",
                " reasonably unambiguous identification to be made  of",
                " neutrons  in  the  highest  2  MeV  of  each neutron",
                " spectrum at each end-point energy.  Correspondingly,",
                " the  8.5  MeV  separation  between the first excited",
                " state  and  second  excited  state  of  Be-8   makes",
                " possible  the  fairly  unambiguous identification of",
                " first excited state in the highest  6  MeV  of  each",
                " neutron  spectrum  once  the  ground  state  neutron",
                " contribution has  been  substracted.  By  comparison",
                " with  the  photoneutron  spectra  from the deuterium",
                " photodisintegration  and  use  of   Partovi's  cross",
                " section for deuterium, differential  cross  sections",
                " for beryllium were obtained."
              ]
            }
          ],
